summary: A U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing the extensive international travel history of Ghislaine Maxwell from 1990 to 1999. The document records 58 entries showing frequent flights between the United States (primarily JFK, MIA) and Europe (primarily London, Paris).

keyFacts: The document is a government-generated travel log (TECS Person Encounter List) showing 58 entries for Ghislaine Maxwell's international travel between 1990 and 1999.
Travel was frequent and transatlantic, with primary routes between New York (JFK) and London (LHR), and Miami (MIA) and London.
Maxwell used multiple travel documents over this period, including a U.S. Alien Registration Card (A), Passport (P), and INSPASS document (I).
The log was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on January 16, 2020, indicating it was compiled as part of a later investigation.
The data shows a pattern of consistent international mobility during the 1990s, a period central to the allegations against Jeffrey Epstein and his associates.
